Resonance parameters have been extracted from
a full R-matrix fit of the capture yields with the
SAMMY code using the Reich-Moore formalism and
including corrections for Doppler and resolution
broadening and for sample multiple scattering and
self-shielding. By means of statistical methods it was
verified that all observed resonances can be
confidently assumed to be s wave.
It was found that the first few resonances of Os-186
and Os-187 could not be fitted because of sample
inhomogeneities, which gave rise to strange resonance
shapes. The effect of sample inhomogeneities could not
be treated with the present version of SAMMY.
